I looked at the existing tickets and this looks like a new issue.

I'm getting an uninitialized value warning on this editwhines line:

            for my $sid (@scheduleids) {
  -->           if ($cgi->param("mailto_type_$sid") == MAILTO_USER) {
                    $arglist->{"mailto_$sid"} = {
                        'type' => 'single',
                    };
                }
            }

I believe what happens is that after I click on "add a new schedule", a new schedule is added with a new $sid.  Yet the new id was not defined in the original form, only the updated form.

